@startuml Deployment Architecture
!theme superhero-outline

node "Development Environment" {
  folder "Source Code" {
    component [Angular Frontend\n(TypeScript + HTML/CSS)] as Angular
    component [ASP.NET Core Backend\n(C# + Entity Framework)] as DotNet
  }
  
  database "Local Database" {
    [SQL Server LocalDB]
  }
}

cloud "GitHub Repository" {
  [Version Control\n(Git)]
}

cloud "Netlify CDN" {
  node "Static Hosting" {
    [Angular Build Output\n(HTML + JS + CSS)] as FrontendBuild
  }
  component [Edge Servers\nGlobal Distribution] as CDN
}

cloud "Microsoft Azure" {
  node "App Service (Linux)" {
    [ASP.NET Core API\n(.NET 8 Runtime)] as API
    [Kestrel Web Server] as Kestrel
  }
  
  database "Azure SQL Database" {
    [Production Database\n(SQL Server)] as ProdDB
  }
  
  component [Application Insights] as Monitor
}

Angular ..> [Version Control] : git push
DotNet ..> [Version Control] : git push

[Version Control] ..> FrontendBuild : ng build --prod\n(auto deploy)
[Version Control] ..> API : dotnet publish\n(manual zip deploy)

FrontendBuild --> CDN : static assets
CDN --> API : HTTPS API calls\n(CORS enabled)
API --> Kestrel : hosting
API --> ProdDB : Entity Framework\nSQL queries
API --> Monitor : telemetry

